data.description: ***SELLER WILL PAY $16,800 FOR CLOSING COSTS OR BUYDOWN......"Discover 2.8 acres of serene Hill Country living in this 2,973-square-foot home, where the wildlife—deer, foxes, and roadrunners—gracefully roam your backyard, creating a nature-lover's paradise. Set amid the stunning natural beauty, you can enjoy the peaceful surroundings from the long front porch and deck, or sip your morning coffee on the stone front patio, all while watching the local fauna at play. As the sun sets, gather around the firepit with friends and family to share stories and create lasting memories. Recent upgrades include new roof shingles, as well as Nest Thermostats for your convenience. Inside, you'll find modern comforts like a powder room with a sleek sink and a luxurious bidet toilet. The spacious kitchen boasts a large island, granite countertops, and ample cabinet space. The master suite features a fireplace and access to the back patio, with an adjoining room perfect for an office, study, nursery, or reading space. Stay energy-efficient with a 3-zone heating and air conditioning system and solar panels, resulting in an average electric bill under $100 per month over the last 10 months. This home offers the ideal balance of nature, comfort, and modern amenities. WHAT A GREAT PLACE TO SEE THE UPCOMING SPRING ECLIPSE!!
